../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:53:- The current order lets the chain spend most of its budget building geometry language before asking whether the argument uses something the averaged model actually destroys.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:54:- The proposed kill condition is too weak. A method can be Tao-blocked even if the criterion does not hold "verbatim" for the averaged model. The real question is whether the proof uses an exact NS-specific transport or algebraic feature unavailable after averaging, rather than generic singular-integral geometry.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:65:- There is also structural bias toward a geometry-first conclusion. The premise assumes the averaged model destroys "fine vortex geometry," but the chain never identifies which exact geometric property is mathematically absent under averaging. That leaves too much room for confirmation bias.
