../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-04.md:5:If regularity fails, the right object may be a minimal blowup profile rather than a sharper local estimate. Kenig-Merle style arguments succeed when one can extract a critical element and then rule it out by rigidity. This chain tests how far current NS profile-decomposition machinery can be pushed and whether any rigidity ingredient survives Tao's averaged-model obstruction.
