../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:5:The attacker is mostly right about the structural weaknesses. The original chain is aimed at a legitimate high-upside question, but it waits too long to demand an estimate-level improvement on the actual NS bottleneck term and it applies the Tao filter too late. The right refinement is not to discard the chain, but to shorten it into a tightly screened obstruction-hunting branch.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:48:### 4. Step 4 applies the Tao filter too late and too one-sidedly
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:52:This is correct. The mission context makes the Tao filter central, not decorative. Since Tao's averaged model preserves energy identity and standard harmonic-analysis structure, any candidate based only on classical algebraic rewriting plus those tools carries a strong prior of being blocked. That screen should be applied before substantial work is spent on a candidate.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:54:The attacker is also right that "not Tao-blocked" is only a necessary condition, not positive evidence. The refined chain has to treat Tao survival as an entry ticket, not as success.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:60:This criticism is substantially right, but it should not be overstated. A reformulation-focused chain is legitimate here because the mission explicitly asks whether the exact NS nonlinearity contains a structural property absent from the averaged model, and the SQG analogy naturally motivates looking for one.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:106:- front-load the Tao filter,
