+Question:
+
+For mission `beyond-de-giorgi`, step `step-006`, identify the strongest local
+repository materials for running the Tao discriminator on the exact-rewrite
+audit fixed in `step-005`.
+
+The inherited audit setup is already frozen:
+
+- architecture:
+  `local-energy flux/localization`
+- bad term:
+  `I_flux[φ] = ∬_{Q_r} (|u|^2 + 2p) u · ∇φ`
+- solution class:
+  suitable weak solutions in the Leray-Hopf energy class with LEI
+- localization protocol:
+  one CKN-style parabolic cutoff, with all projection, Calderon-Zygmund,
+  commutator, and Biot-Savart debt charged explicitly
+- gain currency:
+  `coefficient shrinkage in the fixed localized LEI balance`
+- candidate family:
+  `divergence/stress form`,
+  `Lamb-vector / Helmholtz-projected form`,
+  `vorticity transport / Biot-Savart form`
+
+This step now needs a candidate-by-candidate Tao screen before any estimate
+ledger. Please return concrete findings, not just file paths, on:
+
+1. What exact Navier-Stokes-specific feature each of the three candidates is
+   plausibly claiming to exploit in the local record.
+2. Whether the local record already says that Tao-style averaging destroys,
+   washes out, or preserves that feature, and why.
+3. Where that distinction could enter the fixed localized balance on
+   `I_flux[φ]`, if anywhere, before changing architecture or hypotheses.
